WEBVTT

00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:35.660
Subtitle Provide by dramacool.asia Translator [Admin.@YNG]

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:35.760
[The Guardians]

00:01:36.120 --> 00:01:38.920
[Episode 3]

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:46.080
[Rehearsal Hall]

00:01:52.120 --> 00:01:53.480
[Maxin Theatre,
Public Concession]

00:01:53.480 --> 00:01:54.380
We've checked it out before.

00:01:55.560 --> 00:01:57.020
This is our rehearsal hall.

00:01:57.040 --> 00:01:57.660
To be honest,

00:01:57.680 --> 00:01:58.900
this rehearsal hall of ours

00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:00.820
is bigger than most small theaters.

00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:02.820
Have a seat.

00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:05.260
Here's the thing.

00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:06.660
Right now,

00:02:06.680 --> 00:02:09.540
this place is already rented out.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.260
There's even a show tonight.

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:14.260
No matter how much
you're willing to pay,

00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:15.500
I can't just break the contract.

00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:16.260
Right?

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:20.100
Do you have the final say here?

00:02:20.360 --> 00:02:21.260
Of course I do.

00:02:21.520 --> 00:02:22.780
I'm the owner.

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.170
Pardon my asking,

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:29.340
how big

00:02:29.710 --> 00:02:30.660
is your troupe?

00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:32.450
Not very big.

00:02:32.870 --> 00:02:34.060
Around 20 people.

00:02:37.240 --> 00:02:39.610
In that case,
I'll just be straight with you.

00:02:39.630 --> 00:02:41.100
This place of mine

00:02:41.120 --> 00:02:42.500
isn't something just any troupe

00:02:42.520 --> 00:02:43.610
can afford to rent.

00:02:44.680 --> 00:02:46.780
It's now rented to the Maxin Troupe.

00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:48.940
They're a decent-sized troupe
with 50 to 60 people,

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:50.660
and their shows are always sold out.

00:02:51.520 --> 00:02:52.500
In that case,

00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:53.940
I'll buy it.

00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:05.220
Sorry, everyone.

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:06.940
Today's rehearsal

00:03:07.400 --> 00:03:08.220
is canceled for now.

00:03:08.800 --> 00:03:14.100
Refund the tickets!

00:03:18.840 --> 00:03:19.540
What's going on?

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:20.540
Refunds! Refunds!

00:03:20.560 --> 00:03:21.540
The show's tomorrow,

00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:22.980
why are so many people
asking for refunds?

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:23.820
Why do you want refunds?

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:25.780
[Er Gouzi, Tailor Shop Apprentice]
- Ma'am. - What's wrong?

00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:26.980
Look at this.

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:29.280
[Maxin Theatre]
[Additional Performance Tomorrow]

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:31.240
[A Midsummer Night's Dream, June 23rd]

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:35.660
Oh no, this is terrible!

00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:37.810
That Maxin Troupe is bullying us

00:03:37.830 --> 00:03:39.660
right at our doorstep!

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:41.650
They even put up their own poster

00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:44.100
on our bulletin board,

00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:45.660
and it's for the same day as our show.

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:48.210
If it's not a provocation,

00:03:48.550 --> 00:03:49.970
what else could it be?

00:03:49.990 --> 00:03:50.660
Ma'am,

00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:51.660
calm down.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:52.540
Aren't they putting on

00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:53.970
A Midsummer Night's Dream?

00:03:53.990 --> 00:03:54.650
It's not good.

00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:55.810
That play isn't as good as

00:03:55.830 --> 00:03:57.490
the Romeo and Juliet I chose.

00:03:57.510 --> 00:03:58.940
You bookworm!

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:02.260
Who cares about the play's quality now?

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:04.100
Their theater is bigger than ours,

00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:05.410
their venue is newer,

00:04:05.430 --> 00:04:06.380
more luxurious.

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:07.820
Naturally, the audience

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:09.820
would rather go there.

00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:10.660
Shallow.

00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:12.010
Bookworm!

00:04:13.030 --> 00:04:14.690
Long Er, you jerk!

00:04:14.710 --> 00:04:16.170
Put me down!

00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:18.140
Shout all you want.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:19.370
Scream your lungs out.

00:04:19.390 --> 00:04:21.170
In a bit, you won't have a voice left.

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:24.370
Here.

00:04:26.160 --> 00:04:27.610
Get in there!

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.490
Ms. Xian finally got rid of you.

00:04:29.510 --> 00:04:31.250
Now no one's left
to steal roles from me.

00:04:57.190 --> 00:04:59.140
The way Ms. Xian's calculating

00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:00.930
means we're out of money again.

00:05:00.950 --> 00:05:02.370
And out there,
people are yelling for refunds.

00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:04.170
With internal and external troubles,

00:05:04.630 --> 00:05:07.370
I have no idea if we can hold on.

00:05:08.630 --> 00:05:11.050
Ms. Xian's like calculating
on the attic,

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:12.370
thinking far.

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:27.610
You here to get a refund too?

00:05:28.830 --> 00:05:30.050
Are there many asking for refunds?

00:05:30.950 --> 00:05:31.580
Zhao Fu.

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:35.410
Mr. Gu.

00:05:35.950 --> 00:05:38.250
You're here to see Ms. Xian, I suppose?

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:42.460
Is Ms. Xian busy?

00:05:46.320 --> 00:05:49.880
[Land Ownership Deed]

00:05:55.720 --> 00:05:56.410
What's this about?

00:06:03.160 --> 00:06:05.140
Ms. Xian once saved my life.

00:06:05.390 --> 00:06:06.610
I said before,

00:06:06.830 --> 00:06:09.170
I'd definitely repay that kindness.

00:06:10.120 --> 00:06:12.490
Gratitude is only natural, of course,

00:06:13.240 --> 00:06:14.340
but this gift

00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:17.100
is far too much.

00:06:17.800 --> 00:06:18.930
Not at all, Ms. Xian.

00:06:19.750 --> 00:06:20.850
Compared to Maxin Theatre

00:06:20.870 --> 00:06:22.050
trying to upstage Chaosheng Troupe's

00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:24.410
performance tomorrow night,

00:06:24.430 --> 00:06:26.050
this is nothing.

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:27.290
Of course,

00:06:28.070 --> 00:06:29.050
whether to move or not

00:06:29.070 --> 00:06:30.730
is entirely up to you, Ms. Xian.

00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:33.050
But I've already bought

00:06:33.630 --> 00:06:35.170
this theater.

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:42.250
I see.

00:06:43.390 --> 00:06:44.730
You want Ding Yi.

00:06:47.070 --> 00:06:48.370
I told you,

00:06:48.390 --> 00:06:50.170
I won't let him go with you.

00:06:51.510 --> 00:06:53.250
I won't hand over my people

00:06:53.270 --> 00:06:55.250
to someone dangerous.

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:08.660
Before, I'd never met you,

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:10.020
yet you used

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:11.460
the only pack of sulfa

00:07:11.480 --> 00:07:13.020
in the troupe on me.

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:14.660
So

00:07:15.270 --> 00:07:16.900
these ten packs of sulfa

00:07:17.480 --> 00:07:19.810
are my thanks to you, Ms. Xian.

00:07:40.750 --> 00:07:42.100
That's quite a gesture.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.170
Sulfa is very hard to find now

00:07:45.190 --> 00:07:46.610
on the black market.

00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:50.730
Mr. Gu,

00:07:51.630 --> 00:07:53.540
you're truly resourceful.

00:07:54.430 --> 00:07:55.980
Ms. Xian seems to be well-acquainted

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.730
with black market prices.

00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:00.540
A drop of water shall be returned
with a burst of spring.

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:02.290
I'm sure Ms. Xian

00:08:02.750 --> 00:08:03.730
and your friends

00:08:04.190 --> 00:08:06.370
will find these ten packs of sulfa

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:08.490
very useful.

00:08:09.870 --> 00:08:11.730
They're certainly good things,

00:08:11.750 --> 00:08:13.370
and valuable too.

00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:15.100
But I'm just a troupe leader.

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:17.370
What would I need these medicines for?

00:08:18.630 --> 00:08:21.220
And I don't have any friends

00:08:21.240 --> 00:08:22.730
who'd need such things.

00:08:28.120 --> 00:08:29.580
I just didn't expect it.

00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:31.850
We really underestimated him.

00:08:31.870 --> 00:08:33.220
He's quite grateful.

00:08:35.240 --> 00:08:37.220
You've misunderstood me again.

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.730
The sulfa and the land deed

00:08:39.750 --> 00:08:41.580
are merely my personal thanks

00:08:41.600 --> 00:08:43.100
to you.

00:08:43.870 --> 00:08:44.610
Of course,

00:08:45.510 --> 00:08:46.730
I still want Ding Yi.

00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:49.580
If you'll hand Ding Yi over to me,

00:08:50.240 --> 00:08:51.370
then you

00:08:51.630 --> 00:08:52.730
and your friends

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:54.610
can propose any terms

00:08:54.630 --> 00:08:55.730
you want.

00:09:07.030 --> 00:09:08.130
It's a pity that

00:09:08.150 --> 00:09:09.300
I'm not a landlord.

00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:11.250
And he's not my farmhand.

00:09:11.270 --> 00:09:12.420
I can't make decisions for him.

00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:16.300
After all,

00:09:17.080 --> 00:09:19.010
this is between you and Ding Yi.

00:09:21.550 --> 00:09:22.700
You should talk to him directly.

00:09:23.750 --> 00:09:24.610
Fine.

00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:29.250
Then from today onwards,

00:09:29.670 --> 00:09:31.490
once Ding Yi steps out of

00:09:31.510 --> 00:09:32.980
Chaosheng Troupe's gate,

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:36.530
what happens next will be between us.

00:09:37.270 --> 00:09:38.650
And I hope

00:09:39.790 --> 00:09:40.770
you'll keep your word.

00:10:22.480 --> 00:10:23.340
Suit yourself.

00:10:27.630 --> 00:10:28.180
Wait.

00:10:30.510 --> 00:10:31.340
Is there something else?

00:10:32.750 --> 00:10:33.370
Mr. Gu.

00:10:33.390 --> 00:10:33.980
This...

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:35.850
Once given,

00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:37.650
there's no taking back.

00:10:39.360 --> 00:10:40.060
Keep them.

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:45.820
Ms. Xian.

00:10:47.360 --> 00:10:48.340
Ms. Xian.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.340
Something's wrong, Ms. Xian.

00:10:55.240 --> 00:10:56.490
I'd just driven out of the city

00:10:56.510 --> 00:10:57.610
when four men in suit

00:10:57.630 --> 00:10:59.340
with masks ambushed me.

00:10:59.360 --> 00:11:01.340
Ding Yi

00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:02.490
was taken away by them.

00:11:03.870 --> 00:11:05.220
Gu Yangshan!

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:29.340
These lights feel familiar, don't they?

00:11:30.550 --> 00:11:32.530
You're back to this old place.

00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:36.700
Stay back! Stay back!

00:11:37.840 --> 00:11:38.940
Don't come over!

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:52.040
[Rose Barber Shop]

00:11:54.870 --> 00:11:55.850
Ms. Xian,

00:11:55.870 --> 00:11:56.850
you're here.

00:11:59.120 --> 00:12:00.220
Get my hair done.

00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:00.940
This way, please.

00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:15.760
[Full House]

00:12:17.750 --> 00:12:19.490
Miss, in a hurry?

00:12:19.910 --> 00:12:20.730
Comrade Xiao.

00:12:21.750 --> 00:12:23.610
Gu Yangshan took Ding Yi away.

00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:28.130
[Xiao, Rose Barber Shop Boss, Shanghai Underground Communist]
If he is caught by the Japanese...

00:12:32.270 --> 00:12:33.250
Leave, all of you.

00:12:37.270 --> 00:12:38.130
Don't come over.

00:12:38.150 --> 00:12:38.370
Stay back.

00:12:38.390 --> 00:12:39.010
Turn around.

00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:40.650
Turn around.

00:12:40.670 --> 00:12:41.650
I'm untying the rope.

00:12:43.080 --> 00:12:44.370
Chaosheng Troupe is right across.

00:12:47.720 --> 00:12:48.610
Can't see a thing here.

00:12:49.630 --> 00:12:50.850
This Gu Yangshan

00:12:51.630 --> 00:12:53.820
is the son of Gu Zhengze,

00:12:54.480 --> 00:12:55.580
the deputy commander
of Chongqing Garrison Command.

00:12:56.750 --> 00:12:58.370
He just returned from abroad,

00:12:58.870 --> 00:13:01.610
and is now working for
Shanghai BIS.

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:05.610
He kidnapped Ding Yi

00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:10.010
probably to make him

00:13:10.030 --> 00:13:12.370
continue playing Joseph Lee

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:16.010
and find a breakthrough

00:13:16.270 --> 00:13:18.890
in decrypting that mysterious code
the Japanese are using

00:13:20.150 --> 00:13:21.730
in the Northern Jiangsu battlefield.

00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:26.130
But for Ding Yi,

00:13:26.510 --> 00:13:27.610
this operation is way too dangerous.

00:13:29.030 --> 00:13:30.220
I'm sure you know

00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:31.850
what I'm getting at.

00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:34.180
I'll give you one last chance

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:35.650
to negotiate.

00:13:36.390 --> 00:13:37.060
Tell me.

00:13:37.390 --> 00:13:38.610
How much do you want?

00:13:43.030 --> 00:13:43.610
One?

00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:45.250
Two?

00:13:53.030 --> 00:13:54.730
Five gold bars.

00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:55.980
How about that?

00:13:57.510 --> 00:13:58.130
Five.

00:13:58.510 --> 00:13:59.890
Ding Yi's just an actor.

00:14:00.120 --> 00:14:01.340
He has absolutely no experience

00:14:01.720 --> 00:14:03.420
in intelligence work.

00:14:03.870 --> 00:14:05.460
We can't drag an innocent person

00:14:05.480 --> 00:14:07.460
into something this dangerous.

00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:10.980
Gu Yangshan is being too whimsical.

00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:13.460
I have a plan.

00:14:14.870 --> 00:14:16.100
I'll go find Director William.

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:18.220
What do you think?

00:14:21.240 --> 00:14:21.980
Alright then,

00:14:23.600 --> 00:14:24.980
I'll double it for you.

00:14:26.360 --> 00:14:27.180
Ten?

00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:30.530
You did excellent work
when I put you in charge

00:14:30.840 --> 00:14:32.650
of British intelligence.

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:34.850
Director William is about to step down.

00:14:35.360 --> 00:14:36.100
So I'd say

00:14:36.120 --> 00:14:39.100
your work has been
successfully completed.

00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:40.420
I promised you

00:14:40.670 --> 00:14:42.180
that once the work here is done,

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:44.300
I'd send you to Yan'an.

00:14:46.200 --> 00:14:47.940
Since this code is so important,

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:48.610
I'll stay

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:49.940
to support Ding Yi.

00:14:51.270 --> 00:14:51.770
In that case,

00:14:52.510 --> 00:14:54.010
I need to report this

00:14:54.030 --> 00:14:55.490
unexpected situation
to the organization first.

00:14:56.150 --> 00:14:57.370
Be a little patient.

00:14:58.270 --> 00:14:59.130
Wait for my word.

00:15:02.270 --> 00:15:04.010
I really don't trust the
BIS's methods.

00:15:05.030 --> 00:15:07.650
People in northern Jiangsu
and Ding Yi deserve to live.

00:15:11.390 --> 00:15:12.650
No.

00:15:13.670 --> 00:15:14.890
I won't do it even for ten.

00:15:14.910 --> 00:15:16.770
The more money you offer,
the faster I'll die.

00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:18.250
I'm afraid I'll not live to spend it.

00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:19.100
I'm not doing it.

00:15:21.750 --> 00:15:23.370
Why choose such a place?

00:15:23.390 --> 00:15:24.730
Seems he still doesn't quite trust

00:15:24.750 --> 00:15:26.370
this little stand-in,

00:15:26.390 --> 00:15:28.850
and is figuring that if the stand-in
gets exposed and captured,

00:15:28.870 --> 00:15:31.100
he won't get a chance
to reveal our stronghold.

00:15:33.550 --> 00:15:35.300
Who said you have to die?

00:15:35.510 --> 00:15:37.300
Besides, ten gold bars

00:15:37.320 --> 00:15:39.650
is an exorbitant price
many wouldn't even dare to dream of.

00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:42.490
What's the use of just
being rigorous with details?

00:15:42.510 --> 00:15:43.650
Even if Chairman Chiang came,

00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:44.610
I wouldn't do it.

00:15:46.320 --> 00:15:48.300
What a whimsical man.

00:15:54.150 --> 00:15:55.130
Yangshan,

00:15:55.960 --> 00:15:59.060
looks like you haven't convinced him.

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:01.700
Sir.

00:16:02.840 --> 00:16:03.980
Why are you here?

00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:08.650
Him?

00:16:10.950 --> 00:16:12.340
He's hardly up to the task.

00:16:15.590 --> 00:16:16.570
Sir.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:20.100
A superior, right?

00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:23.100
Sir.

00:16:23.950 --> 00:16:24.930
Sir.

00:16:25.430 --> 00:16:26.930
Sir, you're finally here.

00:16:26.950 --> 00:16:28.170
You have to help me.

00:16:28.190 --> 00:16:29.930
He's with the Anti-Traitor Squad.

00:16:29.950 --> 00:16:31.930
Why not just let him
do his anti-traitor work?

00:16:31.950 --> 00:16:34.170
Why keep hounding us common folks?

00:16:34.190 --> 00:16:35.410
What's the point of this?

00:16:35.430 --> 00:16:36.930
Ask him if you don't believe me.

00:16:36.950 --> 00:16:38.690
I just saved his life.

00:16:38.710 --> 00:16:40.570
People say a drop of water
shall be returned

00:16:40.590 --> 00:16:41.930
with a burst of spring.

00:16:41.950 --> 00:16:43.930
A burst of spring, sir.

00:16:44.400 --> 00:16:45.410
But him?

00:16:45.430 --> 00:16:47.170
He went and tied me up.

00:16:47.400 --> 00:16:49.690
Just now, he even tried to force me

00:16:49.710 --> 00:16:51.170
to die with ten gold bars.

00:16:51.190 --> 00:16:51.930
This...

00:16:52.430 --> 00:16:54.410
This is repaying kindness with enmity!

00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:56.690
I don't have the skills for that.

00:16:56.710 --> 00:16:58.380
Ever since I was little,

00:16:59.160 --> 00:17:00.690
I've been a coward.

00:17:00.710 --> 00:17:02.930
Even a tiny little dog glaring at me

00:17:02.950 --> 00:17:04.420
would scare me so much I'd wet my pants,

00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:05.940
let alone the Japanese.

00:17:05.960 --> 00:17:08.700
What if I slip up in front of

00:17:08.720 --> 00:17:09.940
the Japanese?

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:11.370
What then?

00:17:11.390 --> 00:17:12.940
They wouldn't even need chili water

00:17:12.960 --> 00:17:14.610
or the torture rack.

00:17:14.630 --> 00:17:16.180
Just two slaps,

00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:17.180
and I'd spill everything

00:17:17.200 --> 00:17:18.180
about all of you.

00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:19.700
So you see,

00:17:20.200 --> 00:17:22.130
I'm really just good for nothing.

00:17:22.150 --> 00:17:23.700
I can't do anything.

00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:24.700
Can you please just

00:17:24.720 --> 00:17:26.700
let me go and set me free?

00:17:27.830 --> 00:17:29.740
I'm the only son in my family.

00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:31.290
My mother's back home waiting for me

00:17:31.310 --> 00:17:33.020
to take care of her in her old age.

00:17:44.390 --> 00:17:45.090
Done?

00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:56.220
20.

00:17:57.240 --> 00:18:06.720
[Maxin Theatre]

00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:13.660
Sir.

00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:15.740
He's an actor.

00:18:16.720 --> 00:18:17.420
Six hours.

00:18:17.960 --> 00:18:19.940
Give me six hours and I'll convince him.

00:18:19.960 --> 00:18:21.370
You still need six hours?

00:18:24.150 --> 00:18:26.130
On the Northern Jiangsu battlefield,
every second counts.

00:18:26.390 --> 00:18:28.610
How many more lives do you want
to pay for your delay?

00:18:28.630 --> 00:18:30.700
Even if I gave you 16 hours,
you still couldn't crack it.

00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:34.290
If you can't crack it,
then why not let me try?

00:18:37.350 --> 00:18:39.570
If you could just grab some street punk

00:18:39.590 --> 00:18:40.700
to complete this mission,

00:18:41.240 --> 00:18:44.130
then the Party-State spending
big money to train us

00:18:44.150 --> 00:18:46.090
intelligence officers
would be a total waste.

00:18:47.390 --> 00:18:48.220
And now?

00:18:49.150 --> 00:18:50.180
Have you cracked it?

00:18:50.870 --> 00:18:51.900
Do you have a way?

00:18:56.200 --> 00:18:56.700
Fine.

00:18:57.630 --> 00:18:59.130
If he can complete the mission,

00:18:59.720 --> 00:19:01.420
I will work at your command

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.850
without a word of complaint.

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:07.420
Alright. You said it, I'll remember.

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:18.700
Chief Cao.

00:19:20.150 --> 00:19:21.940
Take a deep breath, deep breath.

00:19:23.590 --> 00:19:25.330
About Joseph Lee's code,

00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:27.500
even if we restore

00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:29.260
our high-powered radio to gather intel,

00:19:29.720 --> 00:19:30.700
how confident are you

00:19:30.720 --> 00:19:32.940
in cracking it within a short time?

00:19:34.390 --> 00:19:35.180
Less than ten percent.

00:19:36.960 --> 00:19:38.180
If it can't be cracked,

00:19:38.960 --> 00:19:40.940
and the Northern Jiangsu battlefield
keeps losing ground,

00:19:41.200 --> 00:19:44.180
do you think the higher-ups
will hold you accountable?

00:19:46.480 --> 00:19:47.940
Exactly.

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:49.700
Let me tell you,

00:19:49.720 --> 00:19:51.180
there's something you don't know.

00:19:51.630 --> 00:19:55.610
The Gu family are a prestigious clan
in the Shanghai area.

00:19:55.630 --> 00:19:56.610
Back in the day, even Chairman Chiang

00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:58.610
was indebted to their family.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:02.180
Just let him mess around.

00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:04.740
If the mission fails,

00:20:04.760 --> 00:20:06.180
he'll take the fall for us.

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:07.370
Chairman Chiang won't

00:20:07.390 --> 00:20:09.180
do anything to our Shanghai Bureau.

00:20:16.440 --> 00:20:18.420
This is how you run the Bureau?

00:20:25.960 --> 00:20:27.660
What an innocent young man.

00:20:28.920 --> 00:20:30.900
When you're my age, you'll understand

00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:33.700
social connections are more
important than getting things done.

00:20:35.440 --> 00:20:37.360
[The Prophecy of Fool]

00:21:10.720 --> 00:21:12.370
Mr. Gu, sorry.

00:21:12.390 --> 00:21:14.740
Tonight's show ends here.

00:21:30.480 --> 00:21:31.810
Cut the useless talk.

00:21:32.550 --> 00:21:33.370
I'm telling you,

00:21:33.790 --> 00:21:35.290
no amount of persuasion will work on me.

00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:37.220
And don't try that

00:21:37.240 --> 00:21:38.460
carrot-and-stick routine on me.

00:21:38.480 --> 00:21:40.530
It won't work here.

00:21:40.550 --> 00:21:40.850
Got it?

00:21:41.440 --> 00:21:42.940
Forget six hours.

00:21:43.390 --> 00:21:45.420
Even six days, six months, or six years,

00:21:46.150 --> 00:21:46.900
I still won't do it.

00:21:46.920 --> 00:21:49.420
I've always been this stubborn.

00:21:50.390 --> 00:21:51.660
So I think you

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:52.940
shouldn't waste your time on me.

00:21:53.200 --> 00:21:55.180
Just send me back straightaway.

00:21:55.870 --> 00:21:57.330
The audience is still waiting
for me on stage.

00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:01.940
Do you really think

00:22:03.440 --> 00:22:04.420
you can return to the stage,

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:07.700
living freely like before?

00:22:13.150 --> 00:22:14.130
I hear you're from the Northeast.

00:22:15.790 --> 00:22:18.530
You came to Shanghai
after the September 18th Incident.

00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:23.770
Yeah.

00:22:23.790 --> 00:22:24.500
So what?

00:22:27.390 --> 00:22:28.660
My mother risked her life

00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:31.660
to escape with me.

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:32.940
So,

00:22:33.390 --> 00:22:34.940
if I lose my life here with you,

00:22:34.960 --> 00:22:36.370
how could I face her?

00:22:37.960 --> 00:22:39.700
After the September 18th Incident,

00:22:40.390 --> 00:22:42.660
you escaped from the Northeast
to Shanghai.

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:45.900
But now, the Northeast
and North China have fallen,

00:22:46.390 --> 00:22:47.900
Central China is in bitter war,

00:22:48.440 --> 00:22:49.940
Shanghai has become a quagmire,

00:22:50.280 --> 00:22:51.660
and the Concessions
are isolated islands.

00:22:52.720 --> 00:22:53.940
Sooner or later,

00:22:54.350 --> 00:22:56.090
the Japanese will march
into the Concession.

00:22:57.110 --> 00:22:58.330
Where will you run then?

00:22:59.440 --> 00:23:00.700
Stop right there.

00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:02.130
Don't talk to me about this.

00:23:02.440 --> 00:23:03.940
Do you really think we common folks,

00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:05.090
who barely went to school,

00:23:05.110 --> 00:23:06.130
understand nothing?

00:23:06.630 --> 00:23:07.610
Why did we run after
the September 18th Incident?

00:23:08.920 --> 00:23:10.940
Because those officers
of the Northeastern Army

00:23:11.070 --> 00:23:12.260
gave up resistance,

00:23:12.280 --> 00:23:14.260
throwing us civilians
into the line of fire.

00:23:15.630 --> 00:23:16.180
I'm telling you,

00:23:16.200 --> 00:23:17.180
if not for sheer luck,

00:23:17.200 --> 00:23:18.660
we wouldn't be alive now.

00:23:21.480 --> 00:23:22.940
Isn't it the same now?

00:23:23.440 --> 00:23:24.260
The Japanese come,

00:23:24.720 --> 00:23:25.740
guns firing.

00:23:26.680 --> 00:23:27.700
But where's Chairman Chiang?

00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:28.610
Where is he?

00:23:29.390 --> 00:23:31.090
Gone, disappeared.

00:23:31.110 --> 00:23:32.130
He hid himself in Chongqing.

00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:33.370
What now?

00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:34.850
You want us common folks

00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:36.090
to take the bullets for him again?

00:23:36.630 --> 00:23:38.420
I'm telling you, I've figured it out.

00:23:38.630 --> 00:23:39.530
The higher the official,

00:23:40.040 --> 00:23:40.660
the faster they run.

00:23:52.590 --> 00:23:53.570
You're not wrong.

00:23:55.960 --> 00:23:58.130
But if everyone thinks this way,

00:24:00.150 --> 00:24:02.130
then our country and homes

00:24:02.760 --> 00:24:03.330
will be destroyed before long.

00:24:05.720 --> 00:24:07.180
Don't try labels on me.

00:24:08.200 --> 00:24:09.700
We are civilians.

00:24:09.720 --> 00:24:11.420
What does war have to do with us?

00:24:18.150 --> 00:24:20.130
Back when the Eight-Nation Alliance
invaded Beijing,

00:24:21.390 --> 00:24:23.130
18,000 troops

00:24:23.390 --> 00:24:24.900
easily captured Beijing,

00:24:24.920 --> 00:24:28.130
which had over a hundred
thousand defenders.

00:24:28.830 --> 00:24:30.260
Besides the authorities'

00:24:30.550 --> 00:24:32.290
inaction and incompetence,

00:24:32.310 --> 00:24:34.530
there were those who led the enemy in,

00:24:34.550 --> 00:24:35.900
opening the gates for them.

00:24:37.920 --> 00:24:39.420
Now the Japanese invaded Nanjing,

00:24:39.550 --> 00:24:41.180
slaughtering 300,000 of our compatriots!

00:24:42.520 --> 00:24:43.900
They're at our doorstep.

00:24:45.350 --> 00:24:46.940
And you want to be the one

00:24:48.070 --> 00:24:49.500
to lead them through the gate?

00:24:51.280 --> 00:24:52.500
When did I lead anyone?

00:24:52.520 --> 00:24:53.500
When did I open the gate?

00:24:53.520 --> 00:24:55.020
Don't slander me!

00:24:55.440 --> 00:24:57.700
By teaching the Japanese as Joseph Lee,

00:24:57.960 --> 00:24:59.940
you've opened the gates for them.

00:24:59.960 --> 00:25:03.180
You've turned your blade
against your own people.

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:05.180
How can you say you haven't?

00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:09.940
I haven't!

00:25:09.960 --> 00:25:11.420
I'm just a commoner.

00:25:11.440 --> 00:25:13.180
I'm just an actor.

00:25:13.200 --> 00:25:14.940
A mere walk-on!

00:25:14.960 --> 00:25:16.420
What's wrong with me making some money?

00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:18.420
I want to eat, I need to survive!

00:25:18.440 --> 00:25:19.420
Is that wrong?

00:25:19.760 --> 00:25:20.740
My mother is still back home,

00:25:20.760 --> 00:25:22.700
waiting for me to return to Baimahu
and care for her!

00:25:22.720 --> 00:25:24.700
But the Chinese civilians
on the Northern Jiangsu battlefield

00:25:24.870 --> 00:25:26.570
are bleeding and dying
because of the code

00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:27.570
you taught them for Joseph Lee.

00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:29.940
And you feel nothing?

00:25:31.960 --> 00:25:34.980
You're noble, you're so capable!

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:37.940
With your privileged background,
you never worry about food or clothing.

00:25:37.960 --> 00:25:39.420
Of course you can feel sad
for the country and the people.

00:25:39.630 --> 00:25:41.940
But us? Can we?

00:25:41.960 --> 00:25:43.420
If you were like us,

00:25:43.440 --> 00:25:44.940
digging in the dirt every day,

00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:46.180
and rolling in the mud,

00:25:46.200 --> 00:25:47.940
you are barely able to survive!

00:25:47.960 --> 00:25:49.610
Then you wouldn't think this way!

00:26:03.960 --> 00:26:05.180
Ding Yi, you're right.

00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:09.700
I am exactly what you said,

00:26:10.150 --> 00:26:11.330
living in luxury

00:26:12.070 --> 00:26:13.420
without worries.

00:26:18.590 --> 00:26:19.130
My father

00:26:19.150 --> 00:26:20.850
is the deputy commander
of Chongqing Garrison Command.

00:26:22.870 --> 00:26:24.330
He is someone who can sit

00:26:24.350 --> 00:26:25.130
with Chairman Chiang,

00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:27.050
drinking tea and watching plays.

00:26:27.390 --> 00:26:29.420
I don't want to hear it!

00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:31.180
I didn't hear anything.

00:26:31.200 --> 00:26:32.180
I don't want to be silenced.

00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:50.660
What I want to say is

00:26:52.200 --> 00:26:53.370
we truly can't

00:26:53.390 --> 00:26:54.660
choose our own birth.

00:26:55.480 --> 00:26:57.460
But we can decide

00:26:57.480 --> 00:26:59.460
what kind of things we want to do.

00:27:05.720 --> 00:27:08.420
In our family, there's a motto.

00:27:09.720 --> 00:27:10.740
Since I was young,

00:27:10.760 --> 00:27:11.700
my father has been teaching me it.

00:27:12.680 --> 00:27:13.700
Want to know what it is?

00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:20.090
Serve the country with utmost loyalty?

00:27:25.720 --> 00:27:26.740
Take the lead in battle.

00:27:30.150 --> 00:27:30.900
So Ding Yi,

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:32.370
no matter what trouble

00:27:32.390 --> 00:27:34.810
or danger you face in the future,

00:27:35.310 --> 00:27:36.180
I will always

00:27:37.680 --> 00:27:39.740
stand in front of you.

00:27:56.960 --> 00:27:58.180
Take a look at this,

00:27:58.590 --> 00:27:59.740
and then decide.

00:28:35.200 --> 00:28:36.980
Who doesn't have a family motto?

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:39.090
I have a family motto too.

00:28:41.590 --> 00:28:42.460
Of the 36 Stratagems,

00:28:43.960 --> 00:28:44.570
running is the best.

00:28:55.680 --> 00:28:56.180
Excuse me.

00:28:58.590 --> 00:28:59.330
You're here.

00:29:00.200 --> 00:29:01.700
I found it.

00:29:02.440 --> 00:29:03.940
Joseph Lee's assistant,

00:29:03.960 --> 00:29:04.700
Charlie Gu,

00:29:05.440 --> 00:29:07.180
holds a British passport.

00:29:07.200 --> 00:29:08.420
He entered four days ago.

00:29:09.590 --> 00:29:11.090
This is his entry record.

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:19.180
Is it genuine?

00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:21.420
Not falsified?

00:29:22.150 --> 00:29:23.180
Unless Joseph Lee's influence

00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:26.610
is powerful enough to control
border and customs officers,

00:29:26.960 --> 00:29:27.940
it can't be falsified.

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:31.180
The military police

00:29:31.200 --> 00:29:32.940
still haven't found
Joseph Lee's whereabouts?

00:29:33.760 --> 00:29:34.180
No.

00:29:35.200 --> 00:29:36.940
We found his car parked
at William's Residence

00:29:36.960 --> 00:29:39.180
of the Municipal Council.

00:29:39.960 --> 00:29:42.420
We can't search British territory,

00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:43.940
so we sent people

00:29:44.200 --> 00:29:45.940
to watch it around the clock.

00:29:47.520 --> 00:29:50.050
No sign of Joseph Lee going in or out.

00:29:52.760 --> 00:29:56.180
We've watched him nearly two months.

00:29:56.200 --> 00:29:57.420
Apart from work,

00:29:57.440 --> 00:29:59.610
he never leaves his room.

00:30:00.200 --> 00:30:02.180
So why suddenly go to

00:30:02.720 --> 00:30:04.610
William's Residence?

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:07.180
Won't let me leave?

00:30:08.960 --> 00:30:09.940
Fine.

00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:12.610
I'll just going to deal with it.

00:30:12.630 --> 00:30:13.940
See who can outlast the other.

00:30:19.200 --> 00:30:21.180
I'll drink your liquor up first.

00:30:22.720 --> 00:30:23.610
Mr. Takeda.

00:30:24.390 --> 00:30:26.130
I think Mr. Joseph Lee's been acting

00:30:26.150 --> 00:30:27.370
very strangely lately.

00:30:29.110 --> 00:30:29.900
Especially

00:30:30.200 --> 00:30:31.610
these past two days,

00:30:31.630 --> 00:30:33.370
he disappeared for so long.

00:30:33.830 --> 00:30:34.900
The military police

00:30:34.920 --> 00:30:36.940
haven't been able to track him at all.

00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:37.940
In this time,

00:30:37.960 --> 00:30:39.330
no one can guarantee

00:30:39.440 --> 00:30:41.180
there hasn't been any

00:30:41.200 --> 00:30:42.610
mistake or accident.

00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:46.700
Let us, in the lilting melody,

00:30:46.720 --> 00:30:49.610
continue this intoxicating night.

